\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. articulata} (Vahl) Masters,{\i  Jour. Roy. Hort. Soc.}{\b  14:} 250 (1892). Pyramidal tree 12-15 m. Cone 8-12 mm in diameter; scales glaucous, triangular, 2 obtuse and 2 acute at the apex, deeply grooved, with a small spine near the apex.{\i  S.E. Spain} ({\i near Cartagena});{\i  Malta.} Hs Si. ({\i N.W. Africa}.)
